Ne ne, minna-san, care to recommend any good manga? I'm currently d/loading mangas and are looking for really good ones. It'll be great if you guys could recommend both good and bad manga titles and give a brief review of it. I'm sure alot of us in here would appreciate it.

Of all the mangas that I've read, my personal favourites are :

Great Teacher Onizuka - it's hilarious yet philosophical at the same time. Couldn't get enough of it. I started out watching the live action GTO before moving on to the anime and finally the manga. Three versions differ from each other in terms of storyline. I prefer the manga way way more than the anime. ^^

FullMetal Alchemist - Again, the manga branches away from the anime mid-way and is totally refreshing ( I watch the anime first ). There's way more hilarious moments in the moment and the secrets behind each character are more detailed.

I am a manga collector, and actually I don't read manga online. I buy them. So you can imagine how many volumes of manga kept in my private room (more than 3000 volumes).

And there are more, but I only have their Mandarin titles. I dunno their english titles.

About the bad manga titles, I would say Shaman King. Becoz the ending is kind of ridiculous. After I read that ending, I realized this series has wasted my money, on buying all 33 volumes of them.

Fortunately, the anime version is much better than the manga version.

And another bad manga title IMO, is Conan The Detective. At first, it's quite interesting. But somehow the content is kind of confusing. And the story is too long, making it started to become boring nowadays.

when I was at my high school, I collects near a thousand volumes of mangas, but sadly almost all of them were thrown out by my brother.

but then, re-collect again... up to 200-300 volumes of manga again. off course at that time all my manga is in malay.

later when I start learning japanese, my 1st manga collection is love hina...... I really recomend this. it's not the ordidary harem manga, but it is the king of harem... lol

then I bought Naruto (not from the first episode, but at the time newest volume)... dont need to tell this, everyone knows naruto.

then, here in japan, I started colecting mangas again...

now I have thousands of volume again... (empires strikes back!)

my recommendation:

Me-Gumi no Daigo aka kisah ahli bomba (who read KREKO knows how great this manga is)

Ahiru no Sora... basketball manga. the best since Slam Dunk finished. Funny, dramatic and full of bask8ball actins. Hope someone willing to transalate this.

Kurosagi aka the black swindler..... read this if you dont want to be cheated. very good manga. really helps for those who learns law and economics

Mobile Suit Gundam: the Origin: written by the character designer of the 1st GUNDAM. after you read this, I guarantee than you realize how BAD the UC series are (esp SEES and Destiny)

Bleach: you know this.

Neon Genesis Evangelion: Eva in manga

Genshiken: great art... and great story. this is what otaku is. an in fact, the story of this manga is nearly same as the creator of love hina, akamatsu ken campus life, said himself.

honey and clover: the best shoujo manga. suitable for non-yaoi manga fan. very nice story and art. and very funny.

Fullmetal Alchemist... manga>TV series... TV series is good, but the manga is beter.

Battle Royale: some hard core action.. gore... and fanservices

Death Note... you know

etc etc etc

Having much more free time then usual, I shall now recommend a few mangas that may or may not pique your interest.

Title:



Oretama

The month of July, 20XX has come, and the world is coming to an end. As prophesied Emanniel, The Queen of Terror will swoop down from the heavens and lay waste to humanity.

In a desperate move an angel was sent down with the intention of sealing her inside a holy stone. He had succeeded.

Well, technically. You see, by a freak chain of events, 19 year old Satou Kohta had become deeply involved in this divine event. Very deeply, for he had the Queen of Terror sealed inside his BALLS.

Yes, you read right, his balls. The fate of the world hangs on his BALLS.

Kohta is then left with a grave warning - "Ejaculate within 30 days, and the world ends"

The old saying "Every time you masturbate, god kills a kitten" comes to mind, albeit this time being a one time deal... with much greater consequences.

In the ultimate endurance test, Kohta now has to abstain for 30 days. Not a big deal right? Elyssie the lesser devil, and Irene the succubus says otherwise.

Will Kohta be able to endure? I know I didn't.

Get it from http://straysscans.devserver.org/ and #strays@irc.irchighway.net

More updates to come.

Added on June 5, 2007, 11:36 amTitle:

100

Yuria Hyaku Shiki

Yuria Type 100

Dr Akiba, a man of science, has a dream. A dream that any man of significant intellect would have. One day, he has attained that dream. After many years of toil, he has created the humanoid pinnacle of modern science.

Arise, Yuria Hyaku Shiki. The ultimate dutch wife.

..............

Yes, Yuria Type 100 was created for that one purpose. Unfortunately, she does not think kindly of this, and runs away into the wilderness of a the world. Barely hours had passed when she was rescued by Kubo Shunsuke from being raped by stray dog (don't ask >_>)

With nowhere else to go, she is taken into his household. There, she fights a continous battle against her inert programming. You see, every fibre of her being wants to get boned. Yet, also having free will she fervently wishes to deny the will of her creator.

Did I also mention that when a phallus is JAMMED into her, it becomes an imprinting that causes her to forever be bound to the owner?

Good luck Yuria. Good luck Shunsuke.

Hourou Musuko (romanize)

The Transient Son (English)

Well, the stories tell bout 5th grader (6th grader) boy name Shuichi Notori, who has the heart of a girl. He has feminine hobby, n most of his friend are all female. His 1st friend when he 1st transfer to new school is tomboyish Yoshino Takatsuki. Both has a secret that no 1 really know, Shuichi Notori always wanted to dress up like a girl, in other word crossdress, while Yoshino Takatsuki does otherwise. Both got hit by some while they were cross-dressing, Shuichi Notori case, his sister's classmate, who she has a feelin of (perhaps) which later on, while Yoshino Takatsuki case, a mature woman (or i should say Okama) which later reveal she is actually he n has a boyfriend (yea they are homosexual). Both of them (the okama n boyfriend) befriend with both Shuichi and Yoshino. Nice story, and i think they are meant for young adult, especially female reader. fun to read with, well atleast i enjoy it. and there arent any excessive yaoi-ness or shounen-ai stuff so, guys, u wont feel awkward readin it.

Planetes





QUOTE

The story of Planetes follows the crew of the DS-12 "Toy Box" of the Space Debris Section, a unit of Technora Corporation. Debris Section's purpose is to prevent the damage or destruction of satellites, space stations and spacecraft from collision with debris in Earth's and the Moon's orbits. They use a number of methods to dispose of the debris (mainly by burning it via atmospheric reentry or through salvage), accomplished through the use of EVA suits.

The episodes sometimes revolve around debris collection itself, but more often the concept of collecting "trash" in space is merely a storytelling method for building character development. The members of the Debris Section are looked down upon as the lowest members of the company and they must work hard to prove their worth to others and accomplish their dreams.

Ongoing plot elements include an upcoming exploratory mission to Jupiter on the new fusion powered ship, Von Braun, and the lead character's decision to join the mission, no matter the cost. Many other plot threads are also developed throughout the series that help to explain each character's motivations and personalities. The Space Defense Front is a terrorist organization that believes mankind is exploiting space without first curing global problems such as mass famine and the widened socio-economic divide on Earth.

One of teh best manga that I've read in years. This and the anime series was overshadowed by the hugely popular Hagane no Renkinjutsushi, thus it was largely ignored outside Japan. I highly recommend this series. The details are so good and the storyline is intruiging.

Summary

Otaku Sakamichi Onoda has just entered high school and plans to join the anime club. In middle school, Onoda didnt have any friends with whom he could talk about anime, games, Akihabara and other otaku things, and he is hoping he can make such friends in the anime club, but he finds out it's been disbanded. In order to reestablish the club he tries to find 4 other people who would like to join.

Since he was a little boy, Onoda has ridden his mamacharia bulky bicycle with a step-through frame mainly used for short rides, such as for casual fun or to pick up groceriesto go to Akihabara every week to check out or buy otaku things. Fellow freshman Shunsuke Imaizumi and bicyclist, while training, notices a boy (Onoda) riding his mamchari up a steep road.

Freshman and road racing cyclist, Shokichi Naruko visits Akihabara to get some Gundam plastic models for his younger brothers and meets Onoda who catches his attention because of the his cycling skill on the mamachari and later find out they go to the same school. Summary for Terra ForMars

With the space program attempting to travel to Mars, 21st century scientists were tasked with warming up the planet so that humans could survive on its surface.
